- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as alignment and parsing. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a method for automatic alignment and parsing, which are important tasks in AI. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed method is based on supervised learning. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is possible as AMR graphs can be used for information retrieval tasks. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is less likely as the paper does not explicitly mention the use of neural or evolutionary methods.
